title: PML-N Nasir Iqbal wins NA-69
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Nasir Iqbal Bosal of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-69 MB Din-II by securing 113,285 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Kausar Parveen an independent candidate who bagged 108,768 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 49.66 per cent in the constituency.
